quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  27,83,And the day when we will gather from every nation a troop of those who said our signs were lies; and they shall be marshalled
  27,84,"until they come, and He will say, 'Did ye say my signs were lies, when ye had compassed no knowledge thereof? or what is it that ye were doing"
  27,85,"and the sentence shall fall upon them for that they did wrong, and they shall not have speech"
  27,86,"Did they not see that we have made the night for them to rest in and the day to see by? verily, in that are signs to people who believe"
  27,87,"And the day when the trumpet shall be blown and all who are in the heavens and the earth shall be startled, save whom God pleases! and all shall come abjectly to Him"
  27,88,"And thou shalt see the mountains, which thou dost deem solid, pass away like the passing of the clouds;- the work of God who orders all things; verily, He is well aware of what ye do"
  27,89,He who brings a good deed shall have better than it; and from the alarm of that day they shall be safe
  27,90,but those who bring an evil deed shall be thrown down upon their faces in the fire. Shall ye be rewarded save for what ye have done
  27,91,"I am bidden to serve the Lord of this country who has made it sacred, and whose are all things; and I am bidden to be of those who are resigned"
  27,92,"and to recite the Qur'an; and he who is guided he is only guided for himself; and he who errs,- say, 'I am only of those who warn"
  27,93,"And say, ' Praise be to God, He will show you His signs, and ye shall recognise them; for thy Lord is not heedless of what ye do"